summary: The module generates a comprehensive lookup table that records whether pairs of standard quantum gates commute for every possible qubit overlap configuration. It focuses on gates that cannot be parameterized, using Qiskit utilities to assess commutation and storing the results in a dictionary keyed by gate pairs and overlap patterns.
business_intent: To supply a readyâ€‘made commutation reference that can be leveraged by quantum circuit compilers and optimizers to quickly determine gate ordering possibilities, thereby improving compilation speed and circuit depth reduction.
